{
  "stem": "18061.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was like from the people that lived in the same building, which wasn't too big.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was about six, seven tenants in the same building.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a small sukkah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had it over there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we ate in that sukkah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, favorite holiday, I would say, Rosh Hashanah--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--was my favorite, because it was the new year.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The new year starts.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the joy between people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was wishing everybody a good year.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was-- that was a favorite, yeah.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I had a bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not-- I had not a huge bar mitzvah, because we were poor people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't celebrate it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father took me in to the shul.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I make-- there wasn't even on a Saturday.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it wasn't-- just he took me in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He showed me how to put on tefillin, if you know what that means.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That is, you know, they put around.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It make from leather, and also on the hat, and make the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's all it was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- I don't even remember [? oh ?] we had whiskey or something to it, because we had no money for it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was the bar mitzvah, not the bar mitzvah that is today, which cost-- [INAUDIBLE] I would say-- $10,000, $20,000, $50,000, [? using ?] with that.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we had synagogue, quite a few.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But mostly they prayed is in shtiblach.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What shtiblach means, a little prayer house.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not exactly a synagogue, a little prayer house, private.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People were there, two or three a room.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They converted one room for the Torah and for the private prayers in the evening.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In mine little house, where I lived, between seven tenants, there was also a little shtiebel, which we made the prayers Friday night, Saturday in that place.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
